Countries and individuals continue to donate money and other resources to the Indian Ocean tsunami victims.
The tsunami killed more than 163,000 people in 11 countries with thousands still missing.
Former President Clinton was named the U.N. special envoy for tsunami relief.
The Asian Development Bank pledged $800 million additional funds for Indonesia for medium-term economic needs beyond tsunami relief.
Saudi Arabia offered the use of five aircraft for relief operations.
To reach isolated regions, Switzerland loaned the U.N. three army helicopters which transported refugees and emergency workers as well as tons of humanitarian aid resources.
